Titulo: Vat photopolymerization 3D printing of NiO-YSZ anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Nevertheless, it remains a significant challenge to prepare three-dimensional electrode structures with finely resolved features.

Sentencas: Herein, we propose a vat photopolymerization (VP) 3D printing process for Nickel Oxide-Yttria Stabilized Zirconia (NiO-YSZ) anode structure of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Vat photopolymerization 3D printing of NiO-YSZ anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A photosensitive NiO-YSZ slurry was prepared with appropriate curing properties, low viscosity, and stability.
Titulo: Vat photopolymerization 3D printing of NiO-YSZ anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Optimal debinding processes, determined through thermo-gravimetric analysis, were employed to prevent green part cracking and deformation.
Titulo: Vat photopolymerization 3D printing of NiO-YSZ anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Microstructural analysis demonstrated a uniform and finely distributed pore structure in the anode.
Titulo: Vat photopolymerization 3D printing of NiO-YSZ anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Remarkably, cells featuring the VP-printed NiO-YSZ anode demonstrated notable performance with peak power densities of 239 mW.cm(-2), 364 mW.cm(-2), and 536 mW.cm(-2) at 750 degrees C, 800 degrees C, and 850 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Vat photopolymerization 3D printing of NiO-YSZ anode for solid oxide fuel cells
